  <body>
    <div id="forena-1" frx:block="forena_help/design_topics"><p>All forena reports are stored as
        regular files in your reports directory, so they can be edited directly using the text
        editor of your choice.&#xA0; The contents of these reports can also be edited using our
        provided editor.&#xA0; Once you navigate to a specific report, the following editing tabs
        are made available:&#xA0;</p><p><strong>Data</strong></p><p>Specify the data you want to
        include in your report.&#xA0; Data blocks are typically provided by developers or site
        administrators.&#xA0; Each data block corresponds to a specific query to a database or
        application.&#xA0; To add data to an existing report, specify the Data Block and a Template
        and choose Preview.&#xA0;</p><p>If the Data Block requires parameters you'll be prompted for
        them in the Parameters field set.&#xA0;</p><p>You may optionally specify a where or order by
        clause to be used with this database query.</p>
      <p>Keep pressing Preview until you see the data that you're expecting in the report
        below.&#xA0; Don't worry if the preview shows too many fields, or isn't quite in the right
        format.&#xA0; You'll be able to control that in the Layout tab later.</p><p>If you need to
        remove a data section from the report, you can check the checkboxes next to the Data Block
        that is currently being displayed and press save.</p><p><strong>Fields</strong></p><p>In the
        fields tab, specify fomatting options for how you want each Field to display when it is used
        in the report.&#xA0; You should see a separate field set for each&#xA0; Field found in the
        report.&#xA0; There are no required data elements here, but an explanation of the options
        are as follows;</p><p>Format - Indicates which custom data format is used to format the data
        (e.g. drupal_date or iso_date).&#xA0;</p><p>Format String - Used to indicate the method in
        the format string.&#xA0; The value here totally depends on the Format indicated (e.g.
        Y-m-d)</p><p>Link - Specify a site relatie URL.&#xA0; When specified, all references to this
        field in the report will be displayed as a links to the URL specified.</p><p>Target -
        Specify the target of the</p><p>Default Value - The value to display when no value is
        present in the data.</p><ul>
        <li id="forena-2" frx:foreach="*">{title}</li>
      </ul></div>
  </body>
</html>
